The abandoned bus on the Stampede Trail in Alaska — made famous by the book and film "Into the Wild" — has been airlifted away.

Hikers from around the world have attempted to visit the bus, but many failed and had to be rescued. Some even died. https://t.co/p5dFdJPJWT
